Description: Fragment of lip, neck and flattened handle of a pottery transport amphora; triangular lip, 1.3 high. Red paint. Clay medium-coarse strong orange-brown; some mica. Circular stamp.
Curator's comments: Pencil '23' (plus). Trimmed. The lip type is North Greek.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1666)
